    "payload": {
      "content": "I have composed a C Major sight-reading etude in 4/4 time. It begins with a two-measure phrase:  \nMeasure 1 consists of the notes C4, E4, G4, C5 (all as quarter notes).\nMeasure 2 repeats these four notes but plays them twice as fast (eight notes).\n\nThe second part introduces some rhythmic variation:\nMeasure 3 contains D4, F4, A4, C5 in quarter notes.\nMeasure 4 takes the same pattern but alternates between eighth and dotted-quarter notes: D4, a rest for an eighth note, F4 held for three quarters, an eighth rest, A4, another eighth rest, and C5 again as a dotted quarter.\n\nThe final two measures return to simplicity, mirroring measure 1 and then concluding with a descending scale from C4 down to E3 in half notes.\n\nPrepare the student by explaining this structure before proceeding. @Madame Pedagogue",
